[b]I'm pretty sure the experienced coders already know this. So... here you go new coding people![/b]

[b]It's really quite simple. Here's the layout, that you'll be using:[/b]
[code]
/*
 * Example by Charles Handson
 */
public class Example {
}
[/code]

[b]The:[/b]
[code]
/*
 *
 */
[/code]
[b]is for making comments. Telling a little information.[/b]

[b]The:[/b]
[code]
public class Example {
}
[/code]
[b]is where your coding will go.[/b]
[b]Example:[/b]
[code]
public class Example {
	if (ExampleIsTutorial) {
		c.codeGame == true;
	}
}
[/code]
[b]The above coding isn't real, just an example.[/b]
[b]Which all together would look like:[/b]
[code]
/*
 * Example by Charles Handson
 */
public class Example {
	if (ExampleIsTutorial) {
		c.codeGame == true;
	}
}
[/code]

[b]Now, in my personal opinion I think that you should only make this for whole new things. Like castle wars.[/b]

[b]Credits:[/b]

[ul][li]100% me![/li][/ul]


[size=12pt][b]EDIT:[/b][/size] [b]I forgot to tell you that you need to change:[/b]
[code]
public class Example {
[/code]
[b]to:[/b]
[code]
public class YourFileName {
[/code]
[b]Also: The Java the class file must be named the same as the public class in order for it to work at all.
